<tr id="L1"><td><a href="#L1">1</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Conifers stand on the slopes down to a lake, where three figures beam down onto a trackway.</td></tr>

<tr id="L2"><td><a href="#L2">2</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Look at those pine trees.</td></tr>

<tr id="L3"><td><a href="#L3">3</a></td><td>KIRK:  And that lake.</td></tr>

<tr id="L4"><td><a href="#L4">4</a></td><td>MCCOY:  I swear that's honeysuckle I smell.</td></tr>

<tr id="L5"><td><a href="#L5">5</a></td><td>KIRK:  I swear that's a little orange blossom thrown in. It's unbelievable. Growth exactly like that of Earth on a planet half a galaxy away. What are the odds on such duplication?</td></tr>

<tr id="L6"><td><a href="#L6">6</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Astronomical, Captain. The relative size, age and composition of this planet makes it highly improbable that it would evolve similarly to Earth in any way.</td></tr>

<tr id="L7"><td><a href="#L7">7</a></td><td>MCCOY:  What in blazes is that?</td></tr>

<tr id="L8"><td><a href="#L8">8</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: A bizarre structure on a dais, with steps leading up to it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L9"><td><a href="#L9">9</a></td><td>KIRK:  Analysis, Spock.</td></tr>

<tr id="L10"><td><a href="#L10">10</a></td><td>SPOCK:  An alien metal of some kind. An alloy resistant to probe. Readings can't even measure its age accurately. These incised symbols are fascinating. Evidently, some form of writing.</td></tr>

<tr id="L11"><td><a href="#L11">11</a></td><td>KIRK:  Any theories about what it is?</td></tr>

<tr id="L12"><td><a href="#L12">12</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Negative, Captain. Structures of this complexity require extremely sophisticated building apparatus, the kind usually found in cultures surpassing or equalling our own.</td></tr>

<tr id="L13"><td><a href="#L13">13</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Meadows and no meteor craters. The whole place is an enigma, biologically and culturally.</td></tr>

<tr id="L14"><td><a href="#L14">14</a></td><td>KIRK:  What's the nearest concentration of life forms, Mister Spock?</td></tr>

<tr id="L15"><td><a href="#L15">15</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Bearing one one seven mark four.</td></tr>

<tr id="L16"><td><a href="#L16">16</a></td><td>KIRK:  And how much time did you say we have to investigate?</td></tr>

<tr id="L17"><td><a href="#L17">17</a></td><td>SPOCK:  If we are to divert the asteroid which is on a collision course with this planet, we must warp out of orbit within thirty minutes. Every second we delay arriving at the deflection point compounds the problem, perhaps past solution.</td></tr>

<tr id="L18"><td><a href="#L18">18</a></td><td>KIRK:  You did say thirty minutes?</td></tr>

<tr id="L19"><td><a href="#L19">19</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Yes, sir.</td></tr>

